1
00:00:01,625 --> 00:00:04,208
(mellow music)

2
00:00:29,181 --> 00:00:32,884
- Hello, I'm Bob Ross,
and for the next 13 weeks,

3
00:00:32,884 --> 00:00:37,168
I'll be your host as we
experience the joy of painting.

4
00:00:37,168 --> 00:00:39,317
This is a fantastic method of painting,

5
00:00:39,317 --> 00:00:41,371
where we use the wet-on-wet technique.

6
00:00:41,371 --> 00:00:43,389
And before I go far into the show,

7
00:00:43,389 --> 00:00:46,929
I'd like to take a few
minutes, and make a dedication.

8
00:00:46,929 --> 00:00:50,469
I would like to dedicate this
show to my beloved friend,

9
00:00:50,469 --> 00:00:54,265
and teacher whom we've all
watched and loved for many years,

10
00:00:54,265 --> 00:00:57,814
on public television, Bill Alexander.

11
00:00:57,814 --> 00:01:00,868
And years ago, Bill taught
me this fantastic technique,

12
00:01:00,868 --> 00:01:04,557
and I feel as though he
gave me a precious gift,

13
00:01:04,557 --> 00:01:07,545
and I'd like to share that gift with you.

14
00:01:07,545 --> 00:01:09,253
So, before we start, let's talk a minute

15
00:01:09,253 --> 00:01:11,685
about the equipment that
we'll be using here.

16
00:01:11,685 --> 00:01:14,817
We're using a stretch canvas,
rather than a canvas board.

17
00:01:14,816 --> 00:01:16,540
The canvas board will absorb your

18
00:01:16,540 --> 00:01:20,206
under-paint very rapidly, and become dry.

19
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:21,968
You need a strong easel,

20
00:01:21,968 --> 00:01:24,440
because we use a lot of pressure here.

21
00:01:24,441 --> 00:01:25,733
And you need an easel that would

22
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:28,685
grip the canvas and hold it securely.

23
00:01:28,685 --> 00:01:30,777
The palette that we use,

24
00:01:30,777 --> 00:01:33,221
we use a large palette that has

25
00:01:33,221 --> 00:01:35,293
a lot of working area in it.

26
00:01:35,293 --> 00:01:36,391
And I'm going to go over

27
00:01:36,391 --> 00:01:38,681
each of the colors that we use here.

28
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:41,096
And they'll be flashed across the screen,

29
00:01:41,096 --> 00:01:42,528
so if you need to write them down,

30
00:01:42,528 --> 00:01:45,588
you can pick them up off the
screen as I talk about them.

31
00:01:45,588 --> 00:01:47,569
So, here we go, let's start right up

32
00:01:47,569 --> 00:01:49,652
here with titanium white.

33
00:01:51,412 --> 00:01:52,412
Thalo green.

34
00:01:53,289 --> 00:01:54,206
Thalo blue.

35
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:56,900
Prussian blue.

36
00:01:58,269 --> 00:01:59,269
Burnt umber.

37
00:02:00,757 --> 00:02:02,007
Van Dyke brown.

38
00:02:03,069 --> 00:02:04,486
Alizarin crimson.

39
00:02:05,349 --> 00:02:06,182
Sap green.

40
00:02:08,842 --> 00:02:09,759
Cad yellow.

41
00:02:10,992 --> 00:02:12,075
Yellow ochre.

42
00:02:13,224 --> 00:02:15,157
Indian yellow.

43
00:02:15,157 --> 00:02:16,657
And permanent red.

44
00:02:18,174 --> 00:02:20,354
Now, these 12 colors we'll use every week.

45
00:02:20,354 --> 00:02:21,974
So, if you wanna have your palette ready,

46
00:02:21,973 --> 00:02:23,637
these are the colors that we'll use.

47
00:02:23,638 --> 00:02:26,234
Also, each week, we'll run
the colors across the screen,

48
00:02:26,234 --> 00:02:29,054
so in case you didn't get all of these,

49
00:02:29,054 --> 00:02:31,093
you can pick them up the next time.

50
00:02:31,093 --> 00:02:32,877
The brushes that we use.

51
00:02:32,877 --> 00:02:34,545
These are natural bristle brushes.

52
00:02:34,545 --> 00:02:37,733
I'm using a two and a half
inch and a one inch brush.

53
00:02:37,734 --> 00:02:40,450
Also, we use an almighty palette knife.

54
00:02:40,449 --> 00:02:42,577
A very big palette knife.

55
00:02:42,578 --> 00:02:45,234
And this palette knife, unlike
traditional palette knives,

56
00:02:45,234 --> 00:02:48,038
is very firm, it's very big.

57
00:02:48,038 --> 00:02:51,262
So, we can do almighty
things very rapidly here.

58
00:02:51,262 --> 00:02:53,250
So, let's do it.

59
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:55,562
Let's paint an almighty
picture right here.

60
00:02:55,562 --> 00:02:57,962
I'm gonna start by dipping the brush into

61
00:02:57,961 --> 00:02:59,613
a little bit of magic white.

62
00:02:59,614 --> 00:03:01,806
Now, this makes the canvas wet,

63
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:05,466
it makes it slick, it allows
the paint to blend in here.

64
00:03:05,466 --> 00:03:08,165
You actually blend the
painting on the canvas.

65
00:03:08,165 --> 00:03:10,894
So, all we do here is
cover the entire canvas

66
00:03:10,894 --> 00:03:12,774
with a thin layer of the magic white.

67
00:03:12,774 --> 00:03:14,530
(bristling)

68
00:03:14,530 --> 00:03:15,362
Alright.

69
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:18,521
Probably the biggest mistake
made when you first start,

70
00:03:18,521 --> 00:03:20,745
is applying too much magic white.

71
00:03:20,746 --> 00:03:23,194
All we want is just a
nice, thin, even coat.

72
00:03:23,193 --> 00:03:24,841
(bristling)

73
00:03:24,842 --> 00:03:25,914
And when you're using large brushes,

74
00:03:25,913 --> 00:03:27,239
this only takes a couple minutes,

75
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,407
so no problem.

76
00:03:29,586 --> 00:03:30,586
There we go.

77
00:03:31,969 --> 00:03:35,719
Look it there, already
we're almost complete.

78
00:03:36,921 --> 00:03:37,754
There.

79
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:40,658
Okay, I just work it back and forth,

80
00:03:40,657 --> 00:03:44,824
and up and down to get a nice
even distribution of color.

81
00:03:47,592 --> 00:03:48,425
Okay.

82
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:53,700
Just about got this canvas
covered with the magic white.

83
00:03:57,801 --> 00:04:00,021
Another big problem that
we run into continually,

84
00:04:00,021 --> 00:04:01,938
is washing the brushes.

85
00:04:03,692 --> 00:04:05,373
Now, I'm gonna wash the brush,

86
00:04:05,373 --> 00:04:07,774
and we wash it with
odorless paint thinner.

87
00:04:07,774 --> 00:04:10,066
And I strongly suggest
that you use odorless,

88
00:04:10,066 --> 00:04:13,234
or you'll run everybody in
the house out in the yard.

89
00:04:13,234 --> 00:04:15,810
You'll be there by yourself.

90
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:18,089
Now, you shake the brush into a box,

91
00:04:18,089 --> 00:04:20,217
and then beat the bristles dry.

92
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,274
Now, if you do this at home,

93
00:04:22,274 --> 00:04:23,817
this is a quick way to redecorate your

94
00:04:23,817 --> 00:04:26,029
living room in a second, so be careful.

95
00:04:26,029 --> 00:04:27,993
Learn how to contain this.

96
00:04:27,994 --> 00:04:30,426
Alrighty, let's do a simple
little picture today,

97
00:04:30,425 --> 00:04:31,750
that'll just give you an idea of how this

98
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,733
fantastic technique works.

99
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:37,005
So, I'm gonna start here with
a little bit of Prussian blue.

100
00:04:37,005 --> 00:04:39,253
And we pull a small amount of paint out,

101
00:04:39,254 --> 00:04:41,218
and beat it into the bristles.

102
00:04:41,218 --> 00:04:43,414
Really work this paint into the bristles.

103
00:04:43,413 --> 00:04:44,765
You're looking for a nice even

104
00:04:44,766 --> 00:04:47,470
distribution of color
throughout the bristles.

105
00:04:47,470 --> 00:04:49,302
And we'll start right up here at the top,

106
00:04:49,302 --> 00:04:50,665
and we just make little "X's",

107
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,850
little crisscross pattern.

108
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:56,194
Come all the way across the top.

109
00:04:56,194 --> 00:04:58,021
There we go.

110
00:04:58,021 --> 00:04:59,870
Now, your brush is picking
up the magic white,

111
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,780
and automatically the
sky is gonna get lighter

112
00:05:01,779 --> 00:05:05,112
in value as it works toward the horizon.

113
00:05:06,254 --> 00:05:07,087
There.

114
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:11,336
Okay, now see how easy that was.

115
00:05:12,298 --> 00:05:13,786
Okay.

116
00:05:13,786 --> 00:05:15,286
And very gently, we'll
just blend this out.

117
00:05:15,286 --> 00:05:17,446
(bristling)

118
00:05:17,446 --> 00:05:19,574
Now, it's very easy to make a sky darker,

119
00:05:19,574 --> 00:05:21,614
but it's a son of a
gun to make it lighter.

120
00:05:21,613 --> 00:05:23,025
If you wanted to make it a little darker,

121
00:05:23,026 --> 00:05:25,194
all you do is add a little more blue.

122
00:05:25,194 --> 00:05:26,646
A little more blue.

123
00:05:26,646 --> 00:05:28,746
This stuff is really strong.

124
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,041
And go right back through
the same procedure.

125
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:33,958
You can darken the sky very easily.

126
00:05:35,033 --> 00:05:35,866
Alright.

127
00:05:38,442 --> 00:05:39,288
Another thing that seems to give

128
00:05:39,288 --> 00:05:43,033
us a lot of problems, is almighty clouds.

129
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:46,317
So, let's spend a second
here and make us a cloud.

130
00:05:46,317 --> 00:05:48,133
And, here we'll use the fan brush.

131
00:05:48,134 --> 00:05:49,949
And, I'm gonna take the fan brush,

132
00:05:49,949 --> 00:05:54,089
and load it full of titanium white paint.

133
00:05:54,089 --> 00:05:54,965
Load it full.

134
00:05:54,966 --> 00:05:57,382
Lot of paint in the bristles.

135
00:05:59,077 --> 00:06:00,425
Okay, now,

136
00:06:00,425 --> 00:06:01,545
we'll go up here and decide where

137
00:06:01,545 --> 00:06:03,933
we want a happy little
cloud to float around.

138
00:06:03,934 --> 00:06:05,362
And you touch the canvas,

139
00:06:05,362 --> 00:06:08,331
and just make little tiny circles.

140
00:06:08,331 --> 00:06:11,170
Just work it, work it, work it.

141
00:06:11,170 --> 00:06:12,069
Do it rapidly.

142
00:06:12,069 --> 00:06:13,781
Push hard and get away from it.

143
00:06:13,781 --> 00:06:15,189
Don't keep working the same area,

144
00:06:15,189 --> 00:06:19,002
all you'll have is a big
cotton ball up in the sky.

145
00:06:19,002 --> 00:06:23,168
Okay, maybe we'll put another
little cloud right over here.

146
00:06:24,108 --> 00:06:28,201
Just to show you how to
make these little clouds.

147
00:06:28,201 --> 00:06:29,574
Okay, now,

148
00:06:29,574 --> 00:06:30,985
with a large brush,

149
00:06:30,985 --> 00:06:32,289
we wanna very gently,

150
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:34,290
blend this out on the bottom down here.

151
00:06:34,290 --> 00:06:36,378
But, without touching the top at all.

152
00:06:36,377 --> 00:06:39,127
So, very gently, just the bottom.

153
00:06:40,262 --> 00:06:42,526
Just blend it a little bit.

154
00:06:42,526 --> 00:06:44,276
Little, tiny circles.

155
00:06:46,326 --> 00:06:47,159
There we go.

156
00:06:47,158 --> 00:06:51,389
Now over here, we'll
blend this one a little.

157
00:06:51,389 --> 00:06:53,081
Now, we'll fluff it.

158
00:06:53,081 --> 00:06:56,262
And, we're just gonna gently lift upward.

159
00:06:56,262 --> 00:06:57,095
And don't worry if you get some of these

160
00:06:57,095 --> 00:06:59,428
little things up in the sky.

161
00:07:01,305 --> 00:07:02,685
Okay.

162
00:07:02,685 --> 00:07:06,721
Now, very gently, we'll hypnotize that.

163
00:07:06,721 --> 00:07:07,721
There we go.

164
00:07:08,574 --> 00:07:10,806
These are very simple,
very basic little clouds.

165
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:12,472
And very easy to do.

166
00:07:13,418 --> 00:07:15,518
Now, if your brush sheds,
like it just did here,

167
00:07:15,517 --> 00:07:17,213
and you get a hair on here,

168
00:07:17,213 --> 00:07:19,230
just take a corner of
your bush and lift it off.

169
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:20,762
Don't spend all day trying to pick it off,

170
00:07:20,762 --> 00:07:23,341
you'll have fingerprints
all over your painting.

171
00:07:23,341 --> 00:07:26,093
Just use a corner of your brush.

172
00:07:26,093 --> 00:07:26,927
Alright.

173
00:07:28,374 --> 00:07:29,994
(water gurgling)

174
00:07:29,994 --> 00:07:32,214
Let's now make an almighty mountain.

175
00:07:32,213 --> 00:07:33,473
Everybody likes mountains.

176
00:07:33,473 --> 00:07:35,229
No matter if you live
in Florida or Alaska,

177
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:36,970
mountains are still pretty.

178
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:39,850
I'ma take a little bit
of the Prussian blue,

179
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:41,858
some van dyke brown,

180
00:07:41,858 --> 00:07:44,602
and a little touch of crimson,

181
00:07:44,601 --> 00:07:45,762
very little crimson.

182
00:07:45,762 --> 00:07:48,218
(scraping)

183
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:51,054
And, we'll mix that up real good.

184
00:07:51,053 --> 00:07:52,537
Now,

185
00:07:52,538 --> 00:07:54,250
all you need to do here is,

186
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:57,473
push this almighty knife
right into the canvas.

187
00:07:57,473 --> 00:07:59,002
Just push.

188
00:07:59,002 --> 00:08:00,822
(scraping)

189
00:08:00,822 --> 00:08:04,988
You're really pushing the
paint right into the fabric.

190
00:08:06,365 --> 00:08:07,199
There.

191
00:08:08,069 --> 00:08:09,134
And all were looking for is just

192
00:08:09,134 --> 00:08:11,968
a basic outline for this mountain.

193
00:08:14,622 --> 00:08:16,442
And you may have noticed by now,

194
00:08:16,442 --> 00:08:18,662
we use no patterns, we do no sketching.

195
00:08:18,661 --> 00:08:22,725
We let this flow right our
of our heart onto the canvas.

196
00:08:22,725 --> 00:08:23,559
There.

197
00:08:23,559 --> 00:08:27,158
Now, with the larger brush,
I'm just gonna pull this down.

198
00:08:27,158 --> 00:08:29,318
One thing about mountains
when you're painting them,

199
00:08:29,317 --> 00:08:30,533
they should always be more distinct

200
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:33,498
at the top than they are at the bottom.

201
00:08:33,498 --> 00:08:35,522
'Cause at the bottom of
the mountain we have mist,

202
00:08:35,522 --> 00:08:37,410
and now we have pollution.

203
00:08:37,409 --> 00:08:40,141
All of these things
diffuse and break up light,

204
00:08:40,142 --> 00:08:43,063
and create the mist at the
bottom of the mountain.

205
00:08:43,062 --> 00:08:44,843
So, once again we allow the magic white

206
00:08:44,844 --> 00:08:47,225
to mix with the paint, and
this happens automatically.

207
00:08:47,225 --> 00:08:48,590
We don't have to worry about it,

208
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:50,269
or think about it.

209
00:08:50,269 --> 00:08:51,436
Let it happen.

210
00:08:53,029 --> 00:08:53,862
Alright.

211
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:57,485
Let's put some snow on
this almighty mountain.

212
00:08:57,485 --> 00:09:00,138
We'll use a little of the titanium white.

213
00:09:00,138 --> 00:09:03,290
And we're gonna start
right up here on this peak,

214
00:09:03,289 --> 00:09:06,169
and just let this paint flow
right down the mountain.

215
00:09:06,169 --> 00:09:08,829
And you want the paint to break like this.

216
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:11,470
So it creates all the
little rocks and stone,

217
00:09:11,470 --> 00:09:15,310
and highlights and
shadows in your mountain.

218
00:09:15,309 --> 00:09:16,709
There.

219
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:19,485
(scraping)

220
00:09:19,485 --> 00:09:20,615
Now,

221
00:09:20,615 --> 00:09:24,615
light's gonna strike right
along this peak also.

222
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:28,254
And maybe,

223
00:09:28,254 --> 00:09:31,004
just a little touch back in here.

224
00:09:32,148 --> 00:09:33,937
Now, let's build some shadows.

225
00:09:33,937 --> 00:09:34,830
And we'll just use a little bit

226
00:09:34,830 --> 00:09:37,497
of the Prussian blue, and white.

227
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,045
Maybe a touch more.

228
00:09:42,046 --> 00:09:43,078
There we go.

229
00:09:43,077 --> 00:09:45,737
(scraping)

230
00:09:45,738 --> 00:09:48,142
Now the shadows will run
in the opposite direction.

231
00:09:48,142 --> 00:09:49,806
We'll start here,

232
00:09:49,806 --> 00:09:54,186
and just let the shadows
run right across like this.

233
00:09:54,186 --> 00:09:55,936
There comes a shadow.

234
00:09:59,923 --> 00:10:01,594
Okay, and we'll put one back here.

235
00:10:01,594 --> 00:10:03,318
And, we've decided this peak,

236
00:10:03,317 --> 00:10:05,193
is behind the mountain.

237
00:10:05,193 --> 00:10:07,233
So, all we do is take this shadow,

238
00:10:07,234 --> 00:10:08,913
and bring it right through.

239
00:10:08,913 --> 00:10:11,860
And automatically, you've
just pushed a mountain around.

240
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:14,269
On this canvas, you're the creator,

241
00:10:14,269 --> 00:10:16,761
anything that you want,
you can build here.

242
00:10:16,761 --> 00:10:17,961
This is your world.

243
00:10:17,961 --> 00:10:20,379
You're dreams come real here.

244
00:10:21,946 --> 00:10:23,360
Alright.

245
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,192
There.

246
00:10:26,806 --> 00:10:28,129
Now, maybe we'll add just a couple

247
00:10:28,129 --> 00:10:30,129
more little peaks in here.

248
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:33,879
Maybe there's a happy
little peak right here.

249
00:10:37,946 --> 00:10:40,446
We put the highlight in first.

250
00:10:42,590 --> 00:10:43,598
And then we give him his own

251
00:10:43,597 --> 00:10:47,109
private little shadow right there.

252
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:50,322
Now, this is a very basic,
simple little mountain.

253
00:10:50,322 --> 00:10:51,625
And as the series progresses,

254
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,442
we'll do some that are a
little more complicated,

255
00:10:53,442 --> 00:10:55,774
if this is too easy for you.

256
00:10:56,855 --> 00:10:57,855
There we go.

257
00:11:00,269 --> 00:11:01,102
Okay.

258
00:11:02,014 --> 00:11:03,878
Now, as we had talked about earlier,

259
00:11:03,878 --> 00:11:05,182
we always want it to be more distinct on

260
00:11:05,182 --> 00:11:07,125
the top than it is on the bottom.

261
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,237
So, using the large brush here,

262
00:11:09,238 --> 00:11:12,526
I'm gonna very gently tap
the bottom of the mountain.

263
00:11:12,525 --> 00:11:15,689
I'm tapping, all I wanna do is diffuse.

264
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:17,773
I don't wanna destroy it.

265
00:11:19,370 --> 00:11:20,370
There we go.

