00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:33,774
Look at that mist.

270
00:11:37,573 --> 00:11:39,906
See, I knew you could do it.

271
00:11:41,361 --> 00:11:42,322
Alright.

272
00:11:42,322 --> 00:11:43,898
I think it's time we had some fun now.

273
00:11:43,898 --> 00:11:45,423
Let's get over here into the sap green,

274
00:11:45,423 --> 00:11:47,744
and just load this brush full of paint.

275
00:11:47,744 --> 00:11:51,072
Just put a lot of paint into the brush.

276
00:11:51,072 --> 00:11:53,935
Just really work it into the bristles.

277
00:11:53,934 --> 00:11:55,278
And,

278
00:11:55,278 --> 00:11:57,053
we're gonna go right along here,

279
00:11:57,053 --> 00:11:58,670
and touch and push.

280
00:11:58,671 --> 00:11:59,504
Just push.

281
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:01,543
Just like so.

282
00:12:04,086 --> 00:12:05,896
This is where you need the almighty easel,

283
00:12:05,897 --> 00:12:07,655
because you're really pushing hard here.

284
00:12:07,654 --> 00:12:11,366
You're pushing the paint
right into the fabric.

285
00:12:11,366 --> 00:12:12,471
Okay.

286
00:12:12,471 --> 00:12:13,471
There we go.

287
00:12:17,380 --> 00:12:19,351
Just push it in.

288
00:12:19,351 --> 00:12:21,720
This is just straight sap green,

289
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,134
and you're bending the bristles.

290
00:12:23,134 --> 00:12:25,279
Most important that you bend the bristles.

291
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:27,980
(bristling)

292
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:28,812
There.

293
00:12:31,538 --> 00:12:32,371
Okay.

294
00:12:34,479 --> 00:12:38,632
Now, I'm gonna go into just
a tiny bit of Prussian blue.

295
00:12:38,631 --> 00:12:41,276
And we'll darken the front here.

296
00:12:41,277 --> 00:12:43,278
As things get closer
to you in a landscape,

297
00:12:43,278 --> 00:12:45,945
they should get darker in value.

298
00:12:47,278 --> 00:12:48,110
Alright.

299
00:12:49,158 --> 00:12:50,408
You know while I'm doin' that,

