00:12:50,408 --> 00:12:53,126
one of the most interesting
things that we see,

301
00:12:53,126 --> 00:12:56,250
as we run across the country
teaching this fantastic method,

302
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:59,639
is people continually say, "I
can't draw a straight line."

303
00:12:59,639 --> 00:13:02,801
"I don't have the talent,
Bob, to do what you're doing."

304
00:13:02,801 --> 00:13:04,223
That's bologna.

305
00:13:04,222 --> 00:13:06,415
Talent is a pursued interest.

306
00:13:06,416 --> 00:13:09,151
In other words, anything that
you're willing to practice,

307
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:10,895
you can do.

308
00:13:10,895 --> 00:13:13,149
And this is no exception.

309
00:13:13,149 --> 00:13:14,894
But it's like driving the car.

310
00:13:14,894 --> 00:13:16,205
At first, it's a little difficult.

311
00:13:16,205 --> 00:13:17,338
You have to learn how to make your hands

312
00:13:17,337 --> 00:13:20,067
and your foots work together.

313
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:23,076
Same thing, and that's what
we're trying to teach you here,

314
00:13:23,076 --> 00:13:24,494
is the technique.

315
00:13:25,341 --> 00:13:27,406
Once you have the technique down,

316
00:13:27,405 --> 00:13:28,750
all you need's a dream in your heart

317
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:31,437
and the desire to put it on canvas.

318
00:13:31,437 --> 00:13:32,747
Okay.

319
00:13:32,748 --> 00:13:33,581
Now,

320
00:13:35,696 --> 00:13:39,187
let's go back here in the
background a little bit.

321
00:13:39,187 --> 00:13:41,828
And, we'll mix up some blue,

322
00:13:41,828 --> 00:13:44,358
this is Prussian blue.

323
00:13:44,359 --> 00:13:48,168
Brown, Van Dyke brown,
in about equal parts.

324
00:13:48,168 --> 00:13:49,053
And sap green.

325
00:13:49,053 --> 00:13:52,097
All three of these are
in about equal parts.

326
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:53,266
And it should look very dark,

327
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:56,386
it should look black on your palette.

328
00:13:56,385 --> 00:13:57,218
Okay.

329
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:01,139
Now, with the fan brush here.

330
00:14:01,139 --> 00:14:02,937
We'll make some, let's
make some little evergreens

331
00:14:02,937 --> 00:14:05,914
back here in front of
this almighty mountain.

332
00:14:05,914 --> 00:14:07,403
And there's many, many ways to make them,

333
00:14:07,403 --> 00:14:08,244
and we'll try to show you a bunch

334
00:14:08,244 --> 00:14:11,115
of ways during this series.

335
00:14:11,115 --> 00:14:13,530
Okay, we load the fan brush full of paint,

336
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:15,932
and decide where you want your tree to be.

337
00:14:15,932 --> 00:14:17,754
You touch the canvas,

338
00:14:17,754 --> 00:14:19,721
turn the brush sideways,

339
00:14:19,721 --> 00:14:21,670
and just begin building a tree.

340
00:14:21,671 --> 00:14:23,682
Back and forth.

341
00:14:23,682 --> 00:14:25,014
Isn't that easy?

342
00:14:26,447 --> 00:14:27,447
Looka there.

343
00:14:28,855 --> 00:14:30,118
And, trees get lonely too,

344
00:14:30,118 --> 00:14:31,129
they need a little friend,

345
00:14:31,129 --> 00:14:34,296
so we'll give him a friend right here.

346
00:14:35,783 --> 00:14:36,616
There.

347
00:14:38,119 --> 00:14:39,283
And you know, sometimes,

348
00:14:39,283 --> 00:14:40,977
you don't wanna a bunch of distinct trees,

349
00:14:40,977 --> 00:14:43,011
you just want indications of trees,

350
00:14:43,011 --> 00:14:44,547
so watch right here.

351
00:14:44,548 --> 00:14:46,037
This is the way to make indications.

352
00:14:46,037 --> 00:14:48,370
All we're doing is touching,

353
00:14:49,234 --> 00:14:50,401
just touching.

354
00:14:52,541 --> 00:14:53,579
And this looks like little trees,

355
00:14:53,578 --> 00:14:55,125
when the painting's
finished it is way, way,

356
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:58,042
they're way back in the background.

357
00:14:59,062 --> 00:15:00,730
And maybe over here.

358
00:15:02,485 --> 00:15:03,407
Just drop these in.

359
00:15:03,407 --> 00:15:07,841
This is, this is such a
free style of painting.

360
00:15:07,841 --> 00:15:08,673
There.

361
00:15:09,971 --> 00:15:13,525
And maybe there's some here
that are a little closer.

362
00:15:13,525 --> 00:15:14,788
There, we'll just drop them in,

363
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:18,587
let them, let them just fall
right off your fan brush.

364
00:15:18,587 --> 00:15:19,587
There we go.

365
00:15:22,231 --> 00:15:23,573
There we go.

366
00:15:23,573 --> 00:15:25,906
(bristling)

367
00:15:27,273 --> 00:15:28,808
Okay, we'll put a little
more dark in here.

368
00:15:28,808 --> 00:15:30,344
You need dark in order to show light,

369
00:15:30,345 --> 00:15:34,066
so here I'm just applying
a little dark color.

370
00:15:34,066 --> 00:15:34,899
Now,

371
00:15:35,775 --> 00:15:38,144
another golden rule that
you need to remember here.

372
00:15:38,144 --> 00:15:40,734
A thin paint will stick to thick paint.

373
00:15:40,734 --> 00:15:42,958
So, I'm adding just a touch of magic white

374
00:15:42,957 --> 00:15:45,817
on my brush here to go
through this thicker paint.

375
00:15:45,817 --> 00:15:47,048
And this will make it a little bit thinner

376
00:15:47,048 --> 00:15:48,985
so it'll stick on top of the thick paint.

377
00:15:48,985 --> 00:15:50,149
This is why we're,

378
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:52,946
we're able to paint wet-on-wet.

379
00:15:52,946 --> 00:15:54,596
Okay, now, let's put
some happy little things

380
00:15:54,596 --> 00:15:57,092
happening back in here.

381
00:15:57,092 --> 00:15:59,716
Just some little bushes and stuff,

382
00:15:59,716 --> 00:16:01,812
here they come, down the hill.

