00:20:06,905 --> 00:20:09,019
little sticks and twigs here and there.

469
00:20:09,019 --> 00:20:09,852
(scratching)

470
00:20:09,852 --> 00:20:12,165
And this helps create
depth in the painting.

471
00:20:12,164 --> 00:20:14,211
It shows different planes.

472
00:20:14,211 --> 00:20:15,512
The more planes you can show,

473
00:20:15,512 --> 00:20:17,995
the deeper the painting will be.

474
00:20:17,996 --> 00:20:22,221
So, we'll just cut a few of them in here.

475
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:23,829
You know, it's interesting,

476
00:20:23,829 --> 00:20:26,261
I was doing this painting
one time at a mall,

477
00:20:26,261 --> 00:20:27,854
and I had a man come along, and he says,

478
00:20:27,854 --> 00:20:29,944
"You know I've been to that location."

479
00:20:29,944 --> 00:20:32,406
He says, "Except it had
a little pond right here,

480
00:20:32,406 --> 00:20:33,754
"if it had a little pond there,

