00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:45,007
All you do is take this almighty brush,

487
00:20:45,008 --> 00:20:46,174
and pull down.

488
00:20:49,565 --> 00:20:52,296
And we'll create a
little pond right there.

489
00:20:52,296 --> 00:20:53,546
It's that easy.

490
00:20:55,611 --> 00:20:56,998
There we go.

491
00:20:56,998 --> 00:21:00,074
(bristling)

492
00:21:00,074 --> 00:21:02,950
And I'm gonna take a little
bit of Prussian blue,

493
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:05,317
just to make this pond
a little bit deeper.

494
00:21:05,317 --> 00:21:08,244
I wanna have enough room for
the trout to live in here.

495
00:21:08,244 --> 00:21:10,327
Just a little bit deeper.

496
00:21:11,926 --> 00:21:13,061
This is one thing that's

497
00:21:13,061 --> 00:21:15,137
so fantastic about this style of painting.

498
00:21:15,137 --> 00:21:17,534
Right, right in mid-stream,
you can change your mind,

499
00:21:17,535 --> 00:21:20,287
you can, you can, completely,

500
00:21:20,287 --> 00:21:23,283
completely change a
painting in just a second.

501
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:24,510
And here, I'm just pulling across

502
00:21:24,510 --> 00:21:26,760
to make it look like water.

503
00:21:27,699 --> 00:21:29,587
Isn't that something?

504
00:21:29,587 --> 00:21:31,955
Now, we'll take just a tiny
bit of the magic white,

505
00:21:31,955 --> 00:21:34,387
(scraping)

506
00:21:34,387 --> 00:21:36,098
and we'll put a little waterline in here.

507
00:21:36,098 --> 00:21:38,515
(scratching)

508
00:21:40,969 --> 00:21:41,802
There.

509
00:21:41,801 --> 00:21:43,184
Just act like you're trying to cut a hole,

510
00:21:43,184 --> 00:21:45,894
right through the canvas.

511
00:21:45,894 --> 00:21:47,228
And, let's take,

512
00:21:49,509 --> 00:21:50,342
and,

513
00:21:51,330 --> 00:21:53,267
I sort of wiped out a couple
of these little bushes here.

